ib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_extends\">extends</span> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/InnerProductSpace/Basic.html#Norm₂\">Norm₂</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> (max u_1 u_2)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"Effectively as `InnerProductSpace 𝕜 E` but it does not requires that `‖x‖^2 = ⟪x,x⟫`. It is\nonly required that they are equivalent `∃ (c > 0) (d > 0), c • ‖x‖^2 ≤ ⟪x,x⟫ ≤ d • ‖x‖^2`. The main\npurpose of this class is to provide inner product space structure on product types `ExF` and\npi types `ι → E` without using `WithLp` gadget.\n\nIf you want to access L₂ norm use `‖x‖₂ := √⟪x,x⟫`.\n\nThis class induces `InnerProductSpace 𝕜 (WithLp 2 E)` which equips `‖·‖` on `X` with L₂ norm.\nThis is very useful when translating results from `InnerProductSpace` to `InnerProductSpace'`\ntogether with `toL2 : E →L[𝕜] (WithLp 2 E)` and `fromL2 : (WithL2 2 E) →L[𝕜] E`.\n\nIn short we have these implications:\n```\n  InnerProductSpace 𝕜 E → InnerProductSpace' 𝕜 E\n  InnerProductSpace' 𝕜 E → InnerProductSpace 𝕜 (WithLp 2 E)\n```\n\nThe reason behind this type class is that with current mathlib design the requirement\n`‖x‖^2 = ⟪x,x⟫` prevents us to give inner product space structure on product type `E×F` and pi\ntype `ι → E` as they are equipped with max norm. One has to work with `WithLp 2 (E×F)` and\n`WithLp 2 (ι → E)`. This places quite a bit inconvenience on users in certain scenarios.\nIn particular, the main motivation behind this class is to make computations of `adjFDeriv` and\n`gradient` easy.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/InnerProductSpace/Basic.html#InnerProductSpace'","kind":"class","line":47,"name":"InnerProductSpace'","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L47-L80"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/InnerProductSpace/Basic.html#«term‖_‖₂»\"><span class=\"name\">«term‖_‖₂»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"L₂ norm on `E`.\n\nIn particular, on product types `X×Y` and pi types `ι → X` this class provides L₂ norm unlike `‖·‖`.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/InnerProductSpace/Basic.html#«term‖_‖₂»","kind":"def","line":42,"name":"«term‖_‖₂»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L42-L43"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/InnerProductSpace/Basic.html#Norm₂.norm₂\"><span class=\"name\">Norm₂</span>.<span class=\"name\">norm₂</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/InnerProductSpace/Basic.html#Norm₂\">Norm₂</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"L₂ norm on `E`.\n\nIn particular, on product types `X×Y` and pi types `ι → X` this class provides L₂ norm unlike `‖·‖`.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/InnerProductSpace/Basic.html#Norm₂.norm₂","kind":"def","line":36,"name":"Norm₂.norm₂","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L36-L36"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/InnerProductSpace/Basic.html#Norm₂.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Norm₂</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">norm₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/InnerProductSpace/Basic.html#Norm₂\">Norm₂</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/InnerProductSpace/Basic.html#Norm₂.mk","kind":"ctor","line":35,"name":"Norm₂.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L35-L35"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">class</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/InnerProductSpace/Basic.html#Norm₂\"><span class=\"name\">Norm₂</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1</div></div>","info":{"doc":"L₂ norm on `E`.\n\nIn particular, on product types `X×Y` and pi types `ι → X` this class provides L₂ norm unlike `‖·‖`.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/InnerProductSpace/Basic.html#Norm₂","kind":"class","line":31,"name":"Norm₂","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L31-L36"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.InnerProductSpace.Calculus","Mathlib.Analysis.InnerProductSpace.Completion","Mathlib.Analysis.InnerProductSpace.ProdL2","Mathlib.Data.Real.CompleteField","Mathlib.Data.Real.StarOrdered"],"instances":[{"className":"InnerProductSpace.Core","name":"instCoreOfInnerProductSpace'","typeNames":[]},{"className":"Inner","name":"instInnerOfInnerProductSpace'","typeNames":[]},{"className":"InnerProductSpace'","name":"instInnerProductSpace'","typeNames":[]},{"className":"InnerProductSpace","name":"InnerProductSpace'.toInnerProductSpaceWithL2","typeNames":["WithLp"]},{"className":"CompleteSpace","name":"InnerProductSpace'.instCompleteSpaceWithLpOfNatENNReal","typeNames":["WithLp"]},{"className":"InnerProductSpace'","name":"instInnerProductSpace'Prod","typeNames":["Prod"]},{"className":"InnerProductSpace'","name":"instInnerProductSpace'Forall","typeNames":[]}],"name":"PhysLean.Mathematics.InnerProductSpace.Basic"}